This paper deals with the classification of hyperspectral images using machine learning techniques. The paper specifically focuses on the extreme learning machine (ELM) and its combination with loopy belief propagation (LBP) for spectral-spatial classification. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
